'''''Tazza: The Hidden Card''''' ({{ko-hhrm|타짜: 신의 손||Tajja: Sineui Son}}; lit. "Tazza: Hand of God") is a 2014 [[South Korea]]n gambling film directed by [[Kang Hyeong-cheol]] based on [[Huh Young-man]] and Kim Se-yeong's [[manhwa]] of the [[Tajja|same name]].<ref>{{cite web|last1=Sunwoo|first1=Carla|last2=Jang|first2=Seo-young|title=Stakes are set high for ''Tazza'' sequel|url=http://koreajoongangdaily.joins.com/news/article/article.aspx?aid=2992826|website=[[Korea JoongAng Daily]]|accessdate=2014-09-20|date=1 August 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last1=Song|first1=Da-in|title=''Tazza'' sequel's success is a sure bet|url=http://koreajoongangdaily.joins.com/news/article/article.aspx?aid=2994189|website=[[Korea JoongAng Daily]]|accessdate=2014-09-20|date=29 August 2014}}</ref>

After Ham Dae-gil enters the gambling world, he is set up as the [[fall guy]] in a crooked deal. To get revenge, he enters a final game which could be fatal to the loser.

